      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": "Freshly squeezed."
    },
    {
      "name": "Coconut Oil",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "Melted."
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "to taste",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Pepper",
      "amount": "to taste",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a small bowl, whisk together grapefruit and lime juice, and set aside.",
    "In a large tandoor-clay-pot or stone-bowl-dolsot, combine coconut oil, salt, and pepper.",
    "Heat the mixture over low heat for 2 minutes, until the oil is warm and fragrant.",
    "Add the thawed prawns, chopped cilantro, and thinly sliced green onions to the pot, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour the grapefruit-lime juice mixture over the top, and stir gently to coat.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional cilantro if desired."
  ],
